      • main

        public static void main​(String[] args)
        Starts the implementation or creation of a jar file. Calls the implement(Class, Path) or implementJar(Class, Path) function depending on the args. Arguments in callable function signatures are converted as needed;
        Parameters:
        args - Array containing [token, root] or [-jar, token, root]

        token - interface that will be implemented;

        root - path of root or .jar directory. in the first case of a set of arguments, implement(Class, Path) is called, in the second - implementJar(Class, Path);
